Reference-contexts: Thus, all interactions between the server and user agent take the form of requests from the agent and responses by the server. Because the HTTP 1.1 specification <ref> [2] </ref> allows arbitrary delay between request and response, it is possible to simulate server-initiated contact by having the user agent keep an open connection to the server while its job is running (if the client dies, it can later reconnect to the server using the global PID for its job).
